  "title": "Human Resource Manager",
  "description": "<p>Job responsibilities:</p>\n<p>1. Responsible for recruitment, performance assessment, training, salary and welfare, employee relations, administration and other daily work;</p>\n<p>2. Prepare personnel recruitment plan and promote its implementation;</p>\n<p>3. Plan and coordinate the overall operation of the personnel department, update and improve the personnel management system;</p>\n<p>4. Excellent communication and public relations skills, with the ability to solve emergencies;</p>\n<p>5. Promotion and implementation of training plans;</p>\n<p>6. Organizational development of personnel.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Position Conditions:</p>\n<p>1. University degree or above, major in human resources, business management, more than 5 years of working experience, more than 3 years of working experience in the same position;</p>\n<p>2. Have a systematic understanding of modern enterprise human resource management mode and practical experience accumulation, have a deep understanding of all functional modules of human resource management, at least proficient in recruitment, performance, training three modules, able to guide the work of each functional module;</p>\n<p>3. Familiar with national and local laws, regulations and policies on human resource management in Singapore and Malaysia;</p>\n<p>4. Excellent communication and public relations ability, with the ability to solve emergencies;</p>\n<p>5. Have good interpersonal skills, organization and coordination skills, communication skills and the ability to solve complex problems；</p>\n<p>6. Have the ability to build team members from 0 to 1；</p>\n<p>7. Fluent in English listening, speaking, reading and writing.</p>\n<p><br></p>",
